<p> The key property of a position in a normal play game is where each player can move to. For example, a <m>4 \times 3</m> board of cut cake has the following possible positions: </p>


<p>If Louise is set to move, she can create </p>
    <ul>
        <li> one <m>1 \times 3</m> and one <m>3 \times 3</m> board </li>
        <li> two <m>2 \times 3</m> boards </li>
    </ul> 
<p> If Richard is set to move, he can create </p>
    <ul>
        <li> One <m>4 \times 1</m> and one <m>4 \times 2</m> board </li>
    </ul>

