<p>It is finally time to answer a critical question. When are two games the same?
</p>

<definition>
    <p> We say that two positions <m>\alpha</m> and <m>\alpha'</m> in (possibly different) normal-play games are <term>equivalent</term> if for every position <m>\beta</m> in any normal play game, the two positions <m>\alpha + \beta</m> and <m>\alpha' + \beta</m> have the same type. We will write <m>\alpha \equiv \alpha'</m> to indicate this.
    </p>
</definition>

