<question> 
    <p>
        Use the definition of equivalent to prove the following (Hint: some of these proofs might be VERY short):
    </p>
<theorem xml:id="Thm-NormalSums">
<p> If <m>\alpha, \beta</m>, and <m>\gamma</m> are positions in normal-play games</p>
<ol>
    <li> <m>\alpha \equiv \alpha</m>.  </li>
    <li> If <m>\alpha \equiv \beta</m> then <m>\beta \equiv \alpha</m>. </li>
    <li> If <m>\alpha \equiv \beta</m> and <m>\beta \equiv \gamma</m> then <m>\alpha \equiv \gamma</m>.  </li>
</ol>
</theorem>
